result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Irineo B. Reyes-Gutierrez was found guilty of OWI (5th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Prior to re-licensing the defendant is to complete an OWI Assessment.

miscConds.notes: Court orders bond on file to be applied. Balance of costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

17CF-116 and 16CF-1 w/17TR-2133 - All Cases Called @ 3:49 PM: Defendant Irineo B. Reyes-Gutierrez in court with attorney Katena Roberts-Turner.  Defendant Irineo B. Reyes-Gutierrez in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Enrique Soria present as Interpreter.  Interpreter oath given by the Court.  Infers competency concern has been withdrawn by Defendant.  Per DA:  Global agreement to resolve today.  Agreement recited.  Counsel stipulate to the report of Dr. Benson as substantive evidence on competency.  Pre-Lim hearing to be waived w/INFO ready to be filed.  16CF-1 SEHR:  327 days of TS credit.  2 yr IC/3 yr ES - consistent with DOC directives with Costs Reimposed.  17CF-116:  OWI 6th - N/C Ct 1.  Ct 2 dismissed.  Ct 3 and Ct 4 DRI.  Argued SEH.  State will cap and argue for a 6 yr bifurcated SEH with credit for 102 days of TS credit with conditions of ES.  Defense is free to argue entire recommendation.  Court confirms with Def that prior competency issue will be withdrawn and Def agrees he is competent to proceed today.  Court accepts withdrawal of competency contest.  Judicial notice take of Dr. Benson's evaluation - record establishes that Def is competent to proceed today.  Defendant agrees with State's recital.  Amended Complaint Stated - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Court entertains waiver of pre-lim hearing as to 17CF-116.  Court accepts knowing and voluntary waiver of pre-lim hearing in its entirety.  Def BOT.  INFO Filed.  INFO Stated - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.    Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant. No impairment on proceeding today.  Agrees with 5 prior convictions as recited by the Court.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained with Immigration Warnings. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  17CF-116 Plea Ct 1 (OWI 6):  GP  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Ct 2 dismissed outright.  Ct Nos 3 and 4 both DRI.   17TR-2133 also DRI.  16CF-1:  Counsel admit receipt of Rev Order and Warrant - No material errors or corrections offered by counsel.  Argument as to SEH recommendation by DA on 16CF-1: 5 yr bifurcated SEH - 2 yr IC/3 yr ES - 327 TS credit.  17CF-116 - 6 yr bifurcated SEH - 3 yrs IC/3 yrs ES - 102 TS credit.   Argument as to SEH recommendation by SPD - argues for diversion from DOC recommendation 17CF-116 18 mos IC/3 yrs ES with concurrent terms.  Statement by Def - None offered.  The Court:  16CF-1: 5 yr imprisonment and bifurcated SEH - 2 yrs IC/3 yrs ES. 327 SEH credit.  17CF-116 - 7 yr term of imprisonment and bifurcated SEH concurrent to period of imprisonment in 16CF-1 - 30 mos or  2-1/2 yrs IC/54 mos or 4 and 1/2 yrs ES.  Net result 2-1/2 IC with 102 days TS credit. concurrent sentences.  Conditions of ES:  The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety - no alcohol whatsoever, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; Complete AODA and any follow thru as recommended; $3000 fine 17CF-116 plus $42.50 blood draw fee - 60 DTP or PP, Department is authorized to withhold any amount or percentage that is found reasonable; 36 mos DL Rev/IID.  16CF-1 - Any remaining balance owed reimposed - 36 mos DL Rev is to be maintained - believes DOT will treat as consecutive sentence on Rev but Court will order concurrent terms.   DNA Sample (on file) and Surcharge ordered by the Court. Hispanic Appeal Rights Given.
Plea hearing on September 12, 2017 at 02:30 pm.
